WEBVTT

00:11:59.939 --> 00:12:02.866
as long as people come back to court
and the money comes back.

00:12:02.890 --> 00:12:05.976
CA: You actually probably didn't know that
when you started this,

00:12:06.000 --> 00:12:08.539
because the assumption
that many people would make is,

00:12:08.563 --> 00:12:11.232
if you bail someone out,
they'd have no skin in the game,

00:12:11.256 --> 00:12:14.271
they probably won't come back to court,
they'll be out of there.

00:12:14.295 --> 00:12:17.887
RS: I'd love to tell you that we were
so smart that we could see the future,

00:12:17.911 --> 00:12:20.966
but we couldn't, and frankly,
it could have gone a different way.

00:12:20.990 --> 00:12:22.712
There was a part of me that thought,

00:12:22.736 --> 00:12:25.931
well, maybe money does make people
come back to court, I'm not sure.

00:12:25.955 --> 00:12:28.879
We weren't sure people would come back;
we didn't really know.

00:12:28.903 --> 00:12:32.633
So we began to use philanthropic dollars
to provide bail assistance for people,